  "name": "Horn of Blasting",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>A <em>horn of blasting</em> is a bright brass trumpet. It can be played as an instrument, granting a +2 item bonus to your Performance check.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">A</span> Interact</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per round</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> When you activate the horn by blowing into it with destructive intent, you create a blast note targeting one creature or object within 30 feet. The blast deals @Damage[3d6[sonic]] damage. (@Check[type:fortitude|dc:28|basic:true] save).</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Activate</strong> <span class=\"action-glyph\">D</span> Interact</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> You can blow even louder to create an intense blast wave in a @Template[type:cone|distance:30] that deals @Damage[8d6[sonic]] damage. Each creature attempts a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:28] save with the following effects.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature takes no damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage and is deafened for [[/br 2d6 #rounds]]{2d6 rounds}.</p>"
    },
